@JessYasBarker It is a broken system. The power goes to the money, and without major structural change there is only so much the population can do. We’ve seen before that a majority vote of the people isn’t even enough to win a presidency. And if a person is TOO outspoken about their rights?

@JessYasBarker This didn’t pass, but it’s an excellent example. States hide your rights from you, ie not telling you that work is legally required to give you paid time off to vote. They don’t tell you about absentee ballets. States with high Latino/Black/Indigenous numbers suffer the worst

@JessYasBarker Voter suppression. In 2020, Texas attempted to pass legislation tht would allow only one voting center per county. That would mean every backwater conservative town got an easy polling place, AND that all of, let’s say Austin, would have only one for millions of voters—>

@ConspiraMo It frustrates me when people say “just leave” to folks in middle America, as if bc of how low the cost of living is here I wouldn’t have to earn triple the amount of money to live at a quarter of the quality I do now on the coasts. Like it’s not feasible for everyone.

My heart goes out to Texas, and for Texans who have been fighting shit like this all along just know that I see you and I won’t let people write you off as unsalvageable. Red-River solidarity from me 🙌

So the inconsistency in characterization of Achilles and Agamemnon (I say these because to me they contradict themselves the most) are almost definitely bc the story was told in a back and forth between multiple bards who all wanted to show THEIR version of them!

Briseis vanished from the story. There is no recorded knowledge of her whereabouts and no documented children from her, in fact it was so sudden that she stopped being mentioned that there are theories that she isn’t a historical figure but an original character of bards 4/

And the timeline! Troy and Babylon were standing at the same time! Rameses the first or second was pharaoh at the time, which means elsewhere in the world during the war we see the beginnings of greater abrahamic organization 3/
The Trojans would not have the same religion nor the same language. They were not Mycenaean or Minoan, they were likely a sort of mish mash of Anatolian with possible Hittite influence (2/)

Homeric stuff is interesting bc it’s like a fictional adaptation of a historical event almost forgotten by the time it was told. The pantheon was different, would have been more heavily Cthonic with Poseidon as the chief deity instead of Zeus (1/)
